The woman threw her husband's body into a pit and poured concrete near Belgorod
In the Belgorod region, a woman confessed to the murder of her own husband, whom she threw into a pit with waste and poured concrete, according to the website of the regional administration of the Investigative Committee of the Russian Federation.
It is noted that the suspect lived in marriage with the murdered since 1999.
In recent years, the husband began to abuse alcohol and after another quarrel, the woman decided to kill.
"When the husband fell asleep, the suspect tied his hands and feet, put a plastic bag on his head and crushed him with a pillow.
When the husband stopped showing signs of life, she wrapped the body in a carpet, carried it out into the yard and hid it in a cesspool.
The next day, I called a concrete mixer and filled the pit with concrete," the department said.
Later, the woman reported that her husband was missing.
Relatives of the deceased appealed to the police, who opened the pit and recovered the body.
The investigation intends to ask the court for the arrest of the suspect.
The investigation of the criminal case is currently ongoing.
